content: Clock Yourself is an amazing app with many uses!. When our community exercise class pivoted to an online platform (Covid) and participants could not use an agility ladder for agility training, we pivoted to collective use of this app and they really like it! Moving forward, we are promoting independent use through a group challenge - and expect to develop a healthy competition that promotes physical activity during wintertime in the North Country of the US.

App only displays in the 0¬∞ portrait orientation! Even Google says apps should support all orientations unless there is a very good reason not to. If only portrait must be supported, then support both 0¬∞ (portrait) and 180¬∞ (reverse portrait). Developers need to remember that there are more devices out there than just phones (some which also need 180¬∞ orientation).
replyContent: Hi Troy. The app is locked to portrait orientation because it was designed with a focus group of older adults who found it confusing if the orientation shifted with movement of the device. It is used by some people with cognitive impairment such as stroke survivors, so we made it user friendly for them.
